1. An electrochemical cell, comprising:
a first electrode comprising a layered perovskite having a general formula:


DAB2O5+δ,


wherein:
D consists of two or more lanthanide elements;
A consists of one or more of Sr and Ba;
B consists of one or more of Co, Fe, Ni, Cu, Zn, Mn, Cr, and Nd; and
δ is an oxygen deficit;
a second electrode comprising a cermet material including at least one metal and at least one perovskite; and
a proton-conducting membrane between the first electrode and the second electrode.

4. The electrochemical cell of claim 1, wherein the layered perovskite of the first electrode comprises:
a first BaO layer;
a first CoO2 layer on the first BaO layer;
a first DOz layer on the first CoO2 layer, wherein z<1;
a second CoO2 layer on the first DOz layer; and
a first second BaO layer on the second CoO2 layer.

17. A structure, comprising at least one layered perovskite having a general formula:


DAB2O5+δ,

wherein D consists of two or more of La, Ce, Pr, Nd, Pm, Sm, Er, Gd, Tb, Dy, Ho, Er, Tm, Yb, and Lu;
A consists of one or more of Sr and Ba;
B consists of one or more of Co, Fe, Ni, Cu, Zn, Mn, Cr, and Nd; and
